The paper concerns the analysis of the Shapley value in matching games, which is a fundamental concept in cooperative game theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). The paper also deals with graph-based cooperative games, which suggests that it could belong to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) or cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The use of polynomial time algorithms and #P-completeness also indicates that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.LG (Machine Learning).
